    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-07-14T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-07-14T11:00:00-05:00" n="404"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d404">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.C115/1430: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-14T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 14, 1940—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 14—11:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2160. Winant informs me very confidentially that he proposes, with support of the
                    Foreign Office here, to move International Labor Office to Canada if the
                    Canadian Government is agreeable and that Massey<note n="22" xml:id="d404fn22"
                        >Vincent Massey, Canadian High Commissioner at London.</note> is today
                    telegraphing Ottawa recommending that an invitation be issued.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennedy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
